\subsection{Metacyclic group}
\begin{definition}\label{group.metacyclic}
\uses{group.monomial,group.nonsplit_product,group.supersolvable,group.z_group}
A metacyclic group is an {{KNOWL("group.nonsplit_product", "extension")}} of a cyclic group by a cyclic group.  All metacyclic groups are {{ KNOWL("group.supersolvable", "supersolvable")}} and in particular {{ KNOWL("group.monomial", "monomial")}}. 

Every {{KNOWL('group.z_group', 'Z-group')}} is metacyclic, but the converse does not hold, as shown by <a href="{{url_for('abstract.index')}}?metacyclic=yes&Zgroup=no">these examples</a>.
\end{definition}


